13/06/2010
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Prime Minister Emil Boc said on Friday (June 11th) that the pensions of retired generals, scientists and other senior civil servants have been cut to help reduce the budget deficit.
According to Boc, as of Friday, the highest pension a former state employee can get is 37,000 lei (8,800 euros) in a country where the average pension is 710 lei (170 euros).
(Romania Libera, Cotidianul, AP, Hotnews.ro - 11/06/10)
